modules.description: This module enables date creation, arithmetic, and comparison operations alongside period manipulation, supporting conversions between date and period types. It provides functions for ISO8601-based formatting, parsing, and precise decomposition of periods into exact days or year-month-day units, working with `date` values for temporal points and `period` values for durations. These capabilities are essential for applications like scheduling systems, financial calculations requiring precise day counts, or generating human-readable time differences.

This module handles date creation, arithmetic, and comparison alongside period manipulation, supporting conversions between date and period types. It offers ISO8601-based formatting, parsing, and precise decomposition of periods into exact days or year-month-day units, working with `date` for temporal points and `period` for durations. Use it to build scheduling systems, perform financial calculations with exact day counts, or generate human-readable time differences. For example, you can calculate the difference between two dates as a period, add days to a date, or format a date in ISO8601 string form.
